-----------------
To run locally
Run MeaningOfLifeNIOPServerLauncher
Run AliceMeaningOfLifeNIOClient
Run BobMeaningOfLifeNIOClient

Provide input to each client in response to prompts. For example, try:
42
29
e
q
--------------------------
To connect to a remote server.
Run MeaningOfLifeNIOClientLauncher, with arguments <host name> <client name>
e.g.
MeaningOfLifeNIOClientLauncher login.cs.unc.edu "john smith"
The name of the local host is "localhost"


In Eclipse, to provide arguments.
Execute Run->Run Configurations...
Right Click Java Application->New
Specify project,main class, and arguments

Or you can just run the main class without arguments, which will create a 
configuration. Terminate program. Now you can execute Run Configurations.. and  edit 
the created configurations and go to arguments tab to supply the args.

 


